HEADWORD: Præcognita
<hw>Pr⟦ae⟧*cog"ni*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praecognitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praecognoscere</ets> to foreknow.
See <er>Pre-</er>, and <er>Cognition</er>.]</ety> <def>This previously
known, or which should be known in order to understand something
else.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

